      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Business administration is one of the most versatile and in-demand degrees available online. Graduates can pursue careers in management, finance, marketing, human resources, and entrepreneurship. The degree is widely offered at affordable online institutions including SNHU, Arizona State University Online, and California Lutheran University."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What can I do with an online psychology degree?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "An online psychology degree prepares you for careers in human resources, social services, healthcare, counseling, and research. It also provides a strong foundation for graduate studies in psychology, counseling, or social work. Programs are available at Walden University, SNHU, and Arizona State University Online."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do employers accept online bachelor's degrees?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. The stigma around online degrees has largely disappeared, especially since the COVID-19 pandemic normalized remote work and learning. Most employers focus on accreditation status and institutional reputation rather than delivery format. Degrees from regionally accredited institutions—whether earned online or on campus—are treated equally by the vast majority of employers."
      }
    }
  ]
};

const articleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
