          <!-- How to Choose -->
          <section id="how-to-choose">
            <div class="section-label">Guidance</div>
            <h2>How to Choose the Right Affordable Online Program</h2>

            <p>With so many options available, it can be difficult to know where to start. Here are the most important factors to evaluate before enrolling:</p>

            <div class="info-grid">
              <div class="info-card">
                <h4>Verify Accreditation First</h4>
                <p>Only enroll in programs from regionally accredited institutions. Confirm accreditation status at <a href="https://www.ed.gov/accreditation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ed.gov</a> or <a href="https://www.chea.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">chea.org</a>.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="info-card">
                <h4>Calculate True Net Cost</h4>
                <p>Use each school's Net Price Calculator and the <a href="https://collegescorecard.ed.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">College Scorecard</a> to compare total program cost, not just cost per credit.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="info-card">
                <h4>Check Transfer Credit Policy</h4>
                <p>Ask how many of your existing credits will transfer. A generous transfer policy can save you a full year or more of tuition.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="info-card">
                <h4>Review Career Outcomes</h4>
                <p>Look at graduation rates and graduate earnings data on the <a href="https://collegescorecard.ed.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">College Scorecard</a> before committing.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

